  "prompt": "Why was the Adidas cotton deodorant discontinued? What did customers think of it?",
  "response": "The Adidas cotton deodorant was discontinued due to low sales and lack of consumer demand. Launched as part of Adidas' line of personal care products, the cotton-scented deodorant failed to gain significant market traction compared to other scents and products in their range.\n\nCustomer opinions on the Adidas cotton deodorant were mixed. Some users appreciated its subtle and fresh scent, finding it a pleasant and effective option for daily use. They praised its long-lasting odor protection and the fact that it was gentle on the skin.\n\nHowever, other customers felt that the cotton scent was too mild or not distinctive enough compared to other fragrances available in the market. Some users also reported that the deodorant's effectiveness in controlling sweat and odor was not as robust as they desired, leading them to switch to other products.\n\nOverall, while the Adidas cotton deodorant had its fans, it did not build a large enough customer base to justify continued production, resulting in its eventual discontinuation.",
